    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 152</em><br/><strong>Price</strong> 100 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> -<br/><strong>Category</strong> Herbs<br/><strong>Gather</strong> DC 18; <strong>Yield</strong> 1 dose<br/><strong>Terrain</strong> temperate or warm forests or plains<br/><strong>Preparation</strong> The amaranth's flowers and stalks must be carefully ground into paste. This requires a successful DC 12 Craft (alchemy) check and 1 hour of work.<br/><strong>Use</strong> A dose of black amaranth paste can be applied to a dead body to slow decay. One dose used on a Tiny or smaller creature delays the onset of decay for 3 days (as per gentle repose). Two doses are needed for Small creatures, 3 for Medium creatures, 6 for Large creatures, 12 for Huge creatures, 24 for Gargantuan creatures, and 48 for Colossal creatures. Each dose applied requires a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity.</p><h2 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\" title=\"The herbalism subsystem is not legal for play; instead a PC with at least one rank in Craft (alchemy) and 1 rank in either Knowledge (nature) or Profession (herbalist) can purchase the herbs in this book at a 10% discount that does not stack with other discounts; if a PC's ranks in these skills are 5 or higher, the discount increases to 15%, and if a PC's ranks in these skills are 10 or higher, the discount increases to 20%\"/>Description</h2><p>Black amaranth grows in small clusters from the remains of the dead.</p>",
